# Project Context
We are building a remote Model Context Protocol (MCP) server using Node.js, Express.js, and TypeScript. 
The server will integrate with the Google Calendar API to list calendars, find time slots, and create events.

# Architecture & Style Guidelines
- Use TypeScript with strict mode enabled.
- Mimic a Spring Boot-style architecture: separate Routes (Controllers), Services (Business Logic), and Config.
- Use async/await. Avoid raw Promises or callbacks.
- Use the official `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` utilizing the `StreamableHTTPServerTransport` for remote communication (SSE transport is deprecated).
- Use the official `googleapis` npm package.

# Error Handling
- Fail fast and throw descriptive custom errors.
- Ensure all Google API errors are caught and transformed into readable MCP tool error responses.

# Dependencies
- express, @modelcontextprotocol/sdk, googleapis, dotenv, cors